        "movement_why": {
          "text": "Monostructural movements (ski erg, bike, double-unders) remove technical barriers and allow the athlete to focus purely on cardiovascular output and pacing. The ski erg emphasizes upper body pulling endurance, the bike targets lower body, and double-unders add a coordination element under fatigue. This develops cardiovascular endurance \u2014 one of Glassman's 10 physical skills \u2014 through varied modalities.",
