          "url_or_ref": "What is Fitness?"
        },
        "loading_why": {
          "text": "The strength block uses 1:1 work:rest intervals (90 seconds on, 90 seconds off) to train aerobic power without full recovery. This ratio keeps the oxidative system engaged while allowing partial phosphocreatine replenishment. The EMOM format in the metcon forces pacing discipline \u2014 athletes must complete work quickly enough to earn rest, training efficiency and recovery management under cardiovascular stress.",
          "source": "Haff & Triplett - NSCA Essentials 4th ed",
          "url_or_ref": "Chapter 3: Energy Systems and Work:Rest Ratios"
        }
      }
