        },
        "loading_why": {
          "text": "The strength complex uses 90-second rest after pull-ups to allow partial upper body recovery while keeping the cardiovascular system engaged from the bike calories. The AMRAP uses moderate loading (24kg/16kg kettlebell, bodyweight movements) and 18-minute duration to ensure oxidative system dominance. Pacing is key \u2014 athletes must resist the urge to sprint early rounds and instead maintain sustainable output across the full time domain.",
          "source": "Haff & Triplett - NSCA Essentials 4th ed",
          "url_or_ref": "Chapter 3: Oxidative system dominant beyond 10 minutes sustained effort"
        }
